article.description: Jasmine James had 15 points and Georgia (No. 11 ESPN/USA Today, No. 12 AP) scored the first 18 points of the game in a 73-48 victory over College of Charleston on Thursday night.
article.headline: Georgia starts fast, runs past College of Charleston
article.linkText: Georgia opens game on 18-0 run, rolls to win
article.story:
ATHENS, Ga. -- Jasmine James had 15 points and Georgia (No. 11 ESPN/USA Today, No. 12 AP) scored the first 18 points of the game in a 73-48 victory over College of Charleston on Thursday night.

Anne Marie Armstrong, Krista Donald and Khaalidah Miller added 10 points apiece for Georgia (3-0).

Megan Fisher led College of Charleston (1-2) with 15 points.

Georgia opened the game with an 18-0 run before Christy Hewatt, scored for College of Charleston, hitting a 3-pointer with 10:45 to go in the first half.

The Cougars missed their first five field-goal attempts, their first four free throws and turned the ball over seven times before scoring.

Georgia's biggest lead of the first half came when Miller's 3 with 5:59 remaining made it 38-7. The Lady Dogs led 44-22 at halftime.

James had a breakaway layup to give Georgia its largest cushion of the game, 67-35.
